Date: Tue, 23 Sep 2003
From: Nomikou Kiki <viruslab@ath.forthnet.gr> [edited]

Re: Bluetongue, sheep - Italy (Sardinia) 20030918.2361
------------------------------------------------------
Bluetongue (BT) virus serotype 2 (BTV 2) has never been isolated in
Greece. In 1979, when we had the 1st incursion of BT in Greece , BTV
4 was isolated.
The 2nd "wave" of incursions of BT in Greece occurred in 1998 until
2001. In 1998, BTV 9 was isolated for the 1st time. In 1999 BTV 4,
BTV 9, and -- for the 1st time, BTV 16 -- were isolated. In 2000,
only BTV 4 was isolated and in 2001, BTV 1 was isolated for the 1st
time.
During the year 2002 and until now there have been no BT outbreaks in
Greece. Altogether, 4 BTV serotypes, namely [chronologically] BTV 4,
BTV 9, BTV 16, and BTV 1 have been isolated in Greece.
--
Nomikou Kiki
Ministry of Agriculture
Centre of Athens Veterinary Institutions
Institute of Infectious and Parasitic Diseases
National Reference Laboratory for Bluetongue, Epizootic Hemorrhagic
Disease of Deer and African Horse Sickness.
