[Dr Nomiku Kiki's remark is in line with ProMED-mail's corrective
posting 20030920.2376, which said: "The writer should have referred
to BTV4 rather than BTV2; the latter virus had originated in North
Africa (see postings 20030111.0091 and 20011122.2864). BTV 4, the
cause of the current outbreak in Sardinia, had indeed been previously
recorded in several Eastern Mediterranean countries including Greece,
Turkey, and Israel".
We are very grateful for this timely update from Greece. As stated in
the table "Second vaccination campaign, 2003" on the web site
<http://www.izs.it/> of Instituto Zooprofilattico Sperimentale
dell'Abruzzo e del Molise "G. Caporale", Teramo, Italy, the use of a
pentavalent vaccine, including BTV serotypes 1,2,4,9, and 16, is
planned for 8 "restricted" territories in Italy. 3 BTV serotypes,
namely BTV2, BTV4, and BTV9, have been identified so far in clinical
cases in sheep in Italy. Antibodies against BTV 16 have been
identified on 31 Jul 2003 in Puglia in sentinel animals; see map
"Bluetongue in Italia, Regione Puglia, Sieroconversione animali
sentinella" on the said web-site (go to PowerPoint "Situazione
epidemiologica ultimi 100 giorni"). The recorded activity of BTV 1 in
Greece explains Italy's decision to include this serotype in the
vaccine. - Mod.AS].
